<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="781" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d781">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1817: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Long</hi></persName>)</head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-16T18:00:00-05:00">October 16, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                    </dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>175. Your 708 October 14, 9 p.m. In reporting on the meeting of
                                    the Diplomatic Corps in Addis Ababa, Engert reported that “it
                                    was decided to request our respective Governments to bring to
                                    the attention of the Italian Government the fact that cities of
                                    Addis Ababa and Diredawa are open and undefended.”</p>
                                <p>In your telegram under reference you state that your
                                    representation referred to an abstention from “bombardment” of
                                    these open cities.</p>
                                <p>Please report whether the representations of all the other
                                    diplomatic representatives also specifically included the word
                                    “bombardment”.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>